<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="131" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1640,1809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1712,1737]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to the recently described species 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen" authorityName="Chen" box="[1019,1290,1712,1737]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Magnimyiolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tengchongnica">
<emphasis box="[1019,1223,1712,1736]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">M. tengchongnica</emphasis>
Chen
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1362,1432,1712,1737]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">China</collectingCountry>
, but differs in having 
<number box="[385,399,1749,1773]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" value="3.0">3</number>
frontal setae and an uninterrupted radial-medial band.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1324,1784,1809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1640,1809]" box="[199,1324,1784,1809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1784,1809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Etymology.</emphasis>
